The '''Imzig''' [[Species/Legends|species]] was a [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]]<ref name="Cloud City Limited" /> [[Humanoid/Legends|Humanoid]]<ref name="CSWE" /> race native to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Couronne/Legends|Couronne]].<ref name="SW article" /> The species differed from base [[Human/Legends|Humans]] through [[Bone/Legends|bony]] ridges surrounding the formers' [[Eye/Legends|eyes]],<ref name="CSWE" /> raised eyebrows, and wider [[Nose/Legends|nostrils]]. At least one was light-skinned, with [[Color/Legends|blue]] mottles on the face, as well as light brown [[Hair/Legends|hair]]. [[Utris M'Toc]] was an Imzig<ref name="Cloud City Limited" /> who hailed from his<ref name="Action Figure Archive">''[[Star Wars: The Action Figure Archive]]''</ref> species' [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]].<ref name="SWI">{{InsiderCite|148|Rogues Gallery|Rogues Gallery: The Cloud City Wing Guards}}</ref>

When a [[Blood/Legends|bloody]] coup occurred on Couronne, M'Toc, who worked as a member of the [[Monarchy/Legends|monarchical]] [[High King's Guard]], fled the planet.<ref name="SWI" /> In [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] [[Occupation of Bespin|occupied]] [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]] on the planet [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]].<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> By that [[Time/Legends|time]], M'Toc had joined Cloud City's [[Bespin Wing Guard/Legends|Wing Guard]], becoming a leader in the [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|security force]],<ref name="Cloud City Limited" /> and he was present on Cloud City during the Imperial takeover.<ref name="SWI" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Imzig species was created by Utris M'Toc's card in the [[1997]] ''[[Cloud City Limited]]'' expansion set of [[Decipher]]'s [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]].<ref name="Cloud City Limited" /> According to ''[[Star Wars]]'' author [[Stephen J. Sansweet]], M'Toc was considered for use in the [[1980]] [[original trilogy]] film, [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']] but was apparently never filmed<ref name="Action Figure Archive" /> and can only be seen in production photos taken on set.<ref name="Action Figure Collection">''[[Star Wars: The Ultimate Action Figure Collection]]''</ref> The makeup was designed by [[Nick Maley]] and then later applied by [[Graham Freeborn]].<ref name="UtrisEmail">{{EmailCite|email=File:MaleyEmailUtris.png|creator=[[Nick Maley]]|date=2025-11-09}}</ref>

